      "narrative": "Latency measured on SimulatedIo backend (in-memory). Point operations are in the same ballpark as SQLite (~10\u201320\u00b5s write) and approaching RocksDB (~5\u201315\u00b5s write), which is notable because TrustDB carries governance metadata (confidence, provenance) that those systems don't. The standout is cross-modal full onboarding at 182\u00b5s \u2014 a query spanning KV, Graph, GIS, and Search that would take 15\u201360ms on a traditional 3-system stack due to network hops and serialization between PostGIS, Neo4j, and Elasticsearch. Temporal decay evaluation at 150M evals/sec is 100\u20131000x faster than app-layer equivalents.",
